Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1 Executive Summary", "Section",
 PageBreakAbove->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.694341537930465*^9, 3.694341550254487*^9}, {
   3.694342355079833*^9, 3.694342363410248*^9}, 3.6943428651189747`*^9, {
   3.6943430193857985`*^9, 
   3.694343019923829*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c84ad9d9-f16d-4ebd-becc-\
c5897e98c089"],

Cell["\<\
This paper investigates the classic Tetrahedron Problem (Project 09), which \
requires determining the areas of the four faces of a tetrahedron given that \
their sum must equal exactly 18 units, and each area must be a strictly \
positive natural integer. 

To solve this discrete geometric problem efficiently, traditional 3D \
brute-force methods were bypassed in favor of a continuous optimization \
approach combined with coordinate descent (cyclic permutation). 

By reducing the problem to a 2D constraint mapping, the complete set of valid \
integer combinations was successfully visualized and identified. 

The mathematical analysis proves that, due to the tetrahedron inequality \
constraint, no single face can exceed a maximum area of 8 units. Furthermore, \
a sensitivity analysis demonstrates how the valid solution space deforms \
under varying global surface constraints.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6551323318137064`*^9, 3.655132346618133*^9}, {
   3.6558834788297663`*^9, 3.655883482105772*^9}, {3.655883581805547*^9, 
   3.655883589683561*^9}, {3.6558837346868153`*^9, 3.655883735919217*^9}, {
   3.694341574232729*^9, 3.694341596852769*^9}, {3.694342244717239*^9, 
   3.694342247462844*^9}, {3.694342333660995*^9, 3.694342343083412*^9}, {
   3.6943424202555304`*^9, 3.694342429299047*^9}, {3.6943424762647333`*^9, 
   3.694342484642213*^9}, {3.694342535512122*^9, 3.694342552269081*^9}, {
   3.6943425832578535`*^9, 3.694342597036641*^9}, {3.694342646046445*^9, 
   3.694342765915301*^9}, {3.694342880577859*^9, 3.694342892973568*^9}, {
   3.920005136849468*^9, 3.9200051373384686`*^9}, {3.990632392594717*^9, 
   3.9906323989862347`*^9}, {3.9906358129725475`*^9, 3.990635817338217*^9}, 
   3.9906358871389637`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"cb0726f4-594f-43e4-8e77-\
5d99a6d9f22b"],

