Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["7 Consequenses and Recommendations", "Section",
 PageBreakAbove->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.694341537930465*^9, 3.694341550254487*^9}, {
   3.694342355079833*^9, 3.694342363410248*^9}, 3.6943428651189747`*^9, {
   3.6943430193857985`*^9, 3.694343019923829*^9}, {3.6943431695433865`*^9, 
   3.694343174763685*^9}, 3.694345609313824*^9, 
   3.920005243579571*^9},ExpressionUUID->"e9bfba02-bbb8-47a6-8db6-\
d4f16dbe0f14"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Based on our analysis, we can draw the following conclusions:\n\n- First, \
for ",
 StyleBox["S = 18",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", the unique integer solution {2, 3, 6, 7} has a quality function value of ",
 StyleBox["f = 26",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The continuous optimum (where A1 = A2 = A3 \[TildeTilde] 3.8) achieves f \
\[TildeTilde] 0, meaning perfectly equal faces. The gap of 26 is entirely due \
to the integer constraint.\n\n- Second, the penalty function method from the \
lecture successfully converges to the constrained continuous optimum as the \
weight w increases. This confirms that the techniques taught in class are \
directly applicable to this type of geometric optimization problem.\n\n- \
Third, the sensitivity analysis shows that for different values of S, the \
best achievable quality varies significantly. Some values of S allow \
solutions with smaller f (more symmetric tetrahedra).\n\n- Fourth, comparing \
our problem to the 2D analogue (Pythagorean triples) shows that finding \
integer solutions to geometric constraint problems is a fundamental challenge \
that spans multiple dimensions.\n\nFor future work, one could apply \
evolutionary algorithms (as covered in the lecture on evolutionary \
optimization strategies) to explore solution spaces in higher dimensions \
where exhaustive search becomes infeasible."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6551323318137064`*^9, 3.655132346618133*^9}, {
  3.6558834788297663`*^9, 3.655883482105772*^9}, {3.655883581805547*^9, 
  3.655883589683561*^9}, {3.6558837346868153`*^9, 3.655883735919217*^9}, {
  3.694341574232729*^9, 3.694341596852769*^9}, {3.694342244717239*^9, 
  3.694342247462844*^9}, {3.694342333660995*^9, 3.694342343083412*^9}, {
  3.6943424202555304`*^9, 3.694342429299047*^9}, {3.6943424762647333`*^9, 
  3.694342484642213*^9}, {3.694342535512122*^9, 3.694342552269081*^9}, {
  3.6943425832578535`*^9, 3.694342597036641*^9}, {3.694342646046445*^9, 
  3.694342765915301*^9}, {3.694342880577859*^9, 3.694342892973568*^9}, {
  3.920005136849468*^9, 3.9200051373384686`*^9}, {3.990682448147463*^9, 
  3.990682477042198*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2a1205f6-5c69-4b47-bba4-\
e02703d86a7d"],

