Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["8 Summary of results", "Section",
 PageBreakAbove->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.694341537930465*^9, 3.694341550254487*^9}, {
   3.694342355079833*^9, 3.694342363410248*^9}, 3.6943428651189747`*^9, {
   3.6943430193857985`*^9, 3.694343019923829*^9}, {3.6943431695433865`*^9, 
   3.694343174763685*^9}, 3.6943456199998417`*^9, 
   3.92000525231802*^9},ExpressionUUID->"8ec61a4a-53fe-4595-983f-\
27013f567dad"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In this term paper, we investigated the Tetrahedron Problem (Project 09). \
The goal was to minimize the quality function ",
 StyleBox["f = (A1-A2)\.b2 + (A1-A3)\.b2 + (A2-A3)\.b2",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", which measures how unequal the three right-triangle faces are, subject to \
the constraint ",
 StyleBox["A1 + A2 + A3 + Sqrt[A1\.b2+A2\.b2+A3\.b2] = 18",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " with all areas being positive integers.\n\nOur main findings:\n\n- The \
unique integer solution is {2, 3, 6, 7}, yielding f = 26.\n\n- The continuous \
optimum is at ",
 StyleBox["A1 = A2 = A3 \[TildeTilde] 3.8",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", giving f \[TildeTilde] 0 (perfect symmetry). The integrality gap is \
therefore 26.\n\n- The penalty function method from the lecture converges to \
the continuous optimum for large penalty weights.\n\n- The Lagrange \
multiplier approach confirms the continuous solution analytically.\n\n- \
Sensitivity analysis across different S values reveals that integer solutions \
exist only for specific S, and the best achievable symmetry varies.\n\n- The \
2D analogue (Pythagorean triples with minimum |a-b|) provides additional \
insight into the structure of the problem.\n\nAll methods used \[LongDash] \
quality functions, penalty methods, Lagrange multipliers, systematic \
enumeration, and visualization \[LongDash] are directly based on techniques \
from the Optimization and Data Analytics course."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6551323318137064`*^9, 3.655132346618133*^9}, {
   3.6558834788297663`*^9, 3.655883482105772*^9}, {3.655883581805547*^9, 
   3.655883589683561*^9}, {3.6558837346868153`*^9, 3.655883735919217*^9}, {
   3.694341574232729*^9, 3.694341596852769*^9}, {3.694342244717239*^9, 
   3.694342247462844*^9}, {3.694342333660995*^9, 3.694342343083412*^9}, {
   3.6943424202555304`*^9, 3.694342429299047*^9}, {3.6943424762647333`*^9, 
   3.694342484642213*^9}, {3.694342535512122*^9, 3.694342552269081*^9}, {
   3.6943425832578535`*^9, 3.694342597036641*^9}, {3.694342646046445*^9, 
   3.694342765915301*^9}, {3.694342880577859*^9, 3.694342892973568*^9}, {
   3.920005136849468*^9, 3.9200051373384686`*^9}, {3.990682049254801*^9, 
   3.9906820714478817`*^9}, {3.9906821465879993`*^9, 3.9906821465879993`*^9}, 
   3.9906821871423473`*^9, {3.990682259449663*^9, 3.990682277947727*^9}, {
